            <scopecontent id="aspace_47a3a810f478a351fea317b4618bfe4d">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Ten photographs of trees in Columbia County, New York, created by Karen Halverson in 2014-2015, and printed as color inkjet prints on Canson Platine Fibre Rag Paper, 20 x 24 inches (51 x 61 centimeters). In the photographs, she introduced flagging tape into the images with a range of colors. The prints are untitled with number sequences provided by Halverson to differentiate images. The collection comprises an edition numbered three of twelve.</p>
            </scopecontent>
